New figures show rise in diabetes rates across London
One in ten people over 40 in the UK are now living with a diagnosis of Type 2
In London, some boroughs have prevalence rates which are among the highest in
the country while other boroughs have the lowest prevalence rates in the
The boroughs with the highest prevalence of diabetes are Harrow (9.58%), Brent
(8.91%), Redbridge (8.66%), Newham (8.57%) and Ealing (8.24%).
